  "text": "Another possible approach to the relative case of GKD theorem goes as follows. This time the arcs considered are not points in the space of arcs X ∞ , but in the relative space of arcs J ∞ (X/Y ) ( [CITATION_1] ). First we remind some basic definitions and properties.",
